sentence: U.S. stock futures were extending Monday's rally, fueled by upbeat earnings from Walmart ( WMT ) and Home Depot ( HD ), as well as stock market gains across Europe as overseas investors discounted the potential impact to the global economy from the Paris attacks.
The first round of Tuesday's economic data was also supportive as the October consumer price index increased by a benign 0.2%, meeting Wall Street expectations.
Excluding the volatile food and fuel segment, prices at the consumer level were also just 0.2% higher.
This morning's remain data includes October capacity utilization and industrial production data, and the National Association of Home Builders (NAHB) housing market index.
Retail earnings have so far been mixed with Walmart and Home Depot reporting positive results, offsetting disappointing results from Dick's Sporting Goods ( DKS ) and Urban Outfitters ( URBN ).
Shares of Angie's List ( ANGI ) are sharply lower after rejecting IAC/Interactive's (IACI) $8.75 per share bid.

(+) OCRX (+17.46%) Announced positive results from the Phase 1 study of OCR-002

(-) CLVS (-6.55%) Downgraded at Goldman Sachs to neutral from buy, lowered price target by $100
